SIMPLE: presidency
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Presidency
<hw>Pres"i*den*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Presidencies</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>pr⟦eacute⟧sidence</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The function or
condition of one who presides; superintendence; control and
care.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The office of president; <as>as, Washington was
elected to the <ex>presidency</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The term during which a president holds his office;
<as>as, during the <ex>presidency</ex> of Madison</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>One of the three great divisions of British India,
the Bengal, Madras, and Bombay Presidencies, each of which had a council
of which its governor was president.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>President</ent>⟦br⟧
